<br>
What the LE membership were told is that a new leader had taken over.  A glance at the guild window confirmed that Chakkan was no longer leader, and had been demoted to officer; and personally, I just assumed that (given Chakkan's lengthy absence) this had happened with Chakkan's consent.<br>
<br>
I'm rather horrified to hear that consent was not given, to be honest.  To log on somebody else's character and remove guildleadership from them strikes me as a fairly serious abuse of trust.<br>
<br>
On the one hand, I feel like Meridian does.  An awfully long time ago, I was leader of the Blood Cult, which has since then advanced to a certain prominence.  Technically, that makes me the owner (from the SoE point of view) of the &quot;Blood Cult&quot; name; if BC were to disband, the only person on Xev who could make a guild called &quot;Blood Cult&quot; would be me.  And I think, technically, if I were to email Sony and ask them to disband the guild, they'd do it, because the name belongs to me.<br>
<br>
I'd never do that, I hasten to add.<br>
<br>
In those days it never occurred to me that the Blood Cult consisted purely of Shadowfrost the cleric.  When I gave up leadership, I recognized that other people might wish to carry on, and even when I left the guild, I certainly did not feel that I had the right to disband it.<br>
<br>
BC was the result of the hard work and effort of an awful lot of people, not just me.  The fact that I stopped being involved in running it, did not make it unviable as a guild, and in fact it's gone an awful long way without any input at all from Shadowfrost.<br>
<br>
So I guess I'm saying that having been a guild leader, and abandoning guild and game, surely doesn't give a person the right to destroy that guild in the process.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, what happened with BC was <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>my</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> choice.<br>
<br>
There was a day when I typed /guildleader Nogi.  (He didn't actually ask for the job - the rest of the officers pretty much convinced him to take it - but that's another story.)  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> typed that, nobody else.<br>
<br>
How would I have felt about it if someone else had logged in my character and typed /guildleader Nogi behind my back?  I don't imagine I would have been thrilled, to say the least.<br>
<br>
There are two sides to most stories, and I imagine the present leaders of the guild will want to speak up about this. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=162740">Shadowfrost</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysidiadrakkenbane>MysidiaDrakkenbane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/724222.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bitch with the Ban Stick</span><br>  Posts: 1926<br> <font color=#330000>(8/18/03 8:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=918.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/1829785.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Farewell for now..</span><hr size=1> Meri,<br>
